title: Drawing, "Male Head, Right Profile"
description: Beneath the curved outline depicting a fleshy forehead, an unbroken line describes a pointed nose, thin lips and rounded chin. A horseshoe shaped outline indicates an empty eye socket. An additional line is diagonally placed in the cheek. To the right of the forehead are several letters imprinted in an antique style.

tombstone.epitaph:
Drawing, "Male Head, Right Profile".
18 x 14.2 cm (7 1/16 x 5 1/2 in.). Gift of Ellen Gustav Jensen. 1956-47-101.
